<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak " data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>Headed by Matthew Hopkinson, the press office aims to provide a helpful service to journalists and reply to all media enquiries within agreed deadlines.</p>

<p>We offer a 24 hour service, with a duty press officer on call to help with urgent enquiries out of hours.</p>

<p>Press officers are bound by the rules of confidentiality and are expressly forbidden - in common with all <abbr title="HM Revenue & Customs">HMRC</abbr> staff - from discussing details of individual taxpayers.</p>

<p>Three desks in the press office deal with national media queries. These are:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Individuals</li>
  <li>Business</li>
  <li>Law Enforcement and Family</li>
</ul>

<p>Regionally, the press office is organised into three teams. These should be the first point of contact for all daytime regional press enquiries.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Wales, Scotland, Northern Ireland, North West England and West Midlands</li>
  <li>North and North East England, South East, South and South West England</li>
  <li>East of England, East Midlands and London</li>
</ul>

<p>Press office structure:</p>

